modules.description: Parses OCaml bytecode from an input channel, invoking callback functions for different sections such as code, data, symbols, and primitives. It processes bytecode dumps generated by the OCaml compiler, allowing inspection or transformation of compiled code elements. Useful for analyzing or modifying low-level bytecode structures during compilation or debugging.

This module parses OCaml bytecode from an input channel, triggering callbacks for sections like code, data, symbols, and primitives. It enables analysis or transformation of compiled code elements by exposing low-level bytecode structures. Key operations include section-specific parsing and data extraction, allowing tasks such as bytecode inspection, modification, or custom processing during compilation or debugging. For example, it can extract symbol information or modify code segments in a compiled OCaml module.
